        <abstract>
            <p>Regrets he cannot sign a memorial for correspondent’s father [Edward Truelove], which states an opinion on a life that is totally unknown to him. Feels that Edward Truelove’s sentence was very harsh [ET was imprisoned and fined for selling "obscene" publications advocating artificial control of conception] even though CD is strongly opposed to all the views expressed.</p> 
<p>Comments on R. D. Owen’s <hi rend="italic">Moral physiology</hi> [1831].</p> 
        </abstract>
